The paper deals with geometric set cover problems, which involve subsets of a geometric space. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of approximation algorithms, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses the use of random subsets and functions, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper involves the use of cuttings and covering, which falls under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
